= Line Breaks

Line break objects create explicit line breaks in text.

== Basic Line Break

This is line one. {{br}}
This is line two.

== Line Break Examples

First line. {{br}}
Second line. {{br}}
Third line.

== Line Break with Formatting

This line has *bold* text. {{br}}
This line has _italic_ text.

== Line Breaks in Paragraphs

This is a paragraph with a line break. {{br}}
The text continues on the next line.

== Line Breaks with Lists

* First item {{br}}
  Continuation of first item
* Second item

== Line Breaks with Code

This is code: `example` {{br}}
This is more code: `another example`

== Line Break Examples

Line one. {{br}}
Line two. {{br}}
Line three.

== Line Breaks with Links

Visit {{link:https://example.com text="Example"}}. {{br}}
Then check {{link:https://github.com text="GitHub"}}.

== Multiple Line Breaks

First paragraph.

Second paragraph with line break. {{br}}
Continuation.

Third paragraph.

== Line Break Syntax

The line break object uses the format: `{{br}}`

This creates a simple HTML `<br>` tag for explicit line breaks.
